"segments": [
{
"start": 0.0,
"end": 3.9,
"text": "There's a form of Chinese written with no Chinese characters at all, in the same alphabet"
},
{
"start": 3.9,
"end": 4.4,
"text": "as Russian."
},
{
"start": 5.02,
"end": 9.08,
"text": "It's spoken in Central Asia, and it quietly proves something a lot of people insist is"
},
{
"start": 9.08,
"end": 9.6,
"text": "impossible."
},
{
"start": 10.48,
"end": 16.24,
"text": "In the 1800s, a group of Chinese Muslims, the Hui, fled unrest and migrated west, settling"
},
{
"start": 16.24,
"end": 18.06,
"text": "in what's now Kyrgyzstan and Kazakhstan."
},
{
"start": 18.76,
"end": 22.14,
"text": "Their descendants are called the Dungan, and they still speak a language descended"
},
{
"start": 22.14,
"end": 26.3,
"text": "from Mandarin Chinese, close enough that a Mandarin speaker can largely follow it."
},
{
"start": 26.82,
"end": 30.64,
"text": "But here's the twist, cut off from China and living in the Soviet world, they stopped"
},
{
"start": 30.64,
"end": 32.1,
"text": "using Chinese characters entirely."
},
{
"start": 32.84,
"end": 36.4,
"text": "Today the Dungan language is written in Cyrillic, letters, just like Russian."
},
{
"start": 36.98,
"end": 41.84,
"text": "Which matters, because people often say Chinese can't be written with an alphabet, that it"
},
{
"start": 41.84,
"end": 44.42,
"text": "needs characters, because too many words sound alike."
},
{
"start": 45.16,
"end": 46.7,
"text": "Dungan is living proof that it can."
},
{
"start": 47.28,
"end": 52.48,
"text": "A complete, working, synodic language, written phonetically with letters, and that quietly"
},
{
"start": 52.48,
"end": 53.38,
"text": "reveals something."
},
{
"start": 53.38,
"end": 58.14,
"text": "The characters and the language aren't the same thing, the spoken Chinese language could,"
},
{
"start": 58.5,
"end": 63.46,
"text": "in principle, be written in letters, and the Dungan have been doing exactly that for generations."
},
{
"start": 64.1,
"end": 68.26,
"text": "So somewhere in Central Asia, people are speaking a kind of Chinese, and writing it"
},
{
"start": 68.26,
"end": 69.52,
"text": "in the alphabet of Russian."
},
{
"start": 70.02,
"end": 74.06,
"text": "A reminder that how a language sounds, and how we choose to write it down, aren't the"
},
{
"start": 74.06,
"end": 74.76,
"text": "same thing at all."
},
{
"start": 75.18,
"end": 76.54,
"text": "Want to actually start learning Chinese?"
},
{
"start": 77.08,
"end": 81.18,
"text": "Discover thousands of free exercises and more learning content on stacktags.io."
}
]
}